American singer Ciara and her husband Russell Wilson are expecting their third child. The “Level Up” singer announced the news on her Instagram page on which she shared a photo of herself posing in a bikini while baring her baby bump. She captioned the photo, “Number 3”.   Number 3. : @DangeRussWilson A post shared by  Ciara (@ciara) on Jan 30, 2020 at 5:20am PST  Wilson also shared a version of the photo, taken instead as a selfie with Ciara in the background.   Number 3. @Ciara A post shared by  Russell Wilson (@dangerusswilson) on Jan 30, 2020 at 5:37am PST  The couple along with the children are currently vacationing in the Turks and Caicos Islands. Ciara and Wilson began dating in early 2015 and announced their engagement on March 11, 2016. They were married on July 6, 2016, at Peckforton Castle in Cheshire, England. Together, they have one child, a daughter, Sienna Princess who was born on April 28, 2017. Ciara also has a son, Future Zahir Wilburn who was born on May 19, 2014, from her previous relationship with rapper Future. Ciara and Future were engaged in October 2013 but ended the engagement in August 2014. 